UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Jason Michael CARPENTER, Defendant-Appellant. No. 06-20178

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 12, 2007. James Lee Turner, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Southern District of Texas, Houston, TX, for PlaintiffAppellee. Jason Michael Carpenter, Beaumont, TX, pro se. Leslie Donovan Banks, Houston, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Before REAVLEY, BARKSDALE, and GARZA, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Jason Michael Carpenter has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Carpenter has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no non-frivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
